# Note on old module URLs (before 8-module restructure, 2026-03):
# Old /modul/1/ split into /modul/1/ (Krankheitsbild) + /modul/2/ (Belastung)
# Old /modul/2/ (Beziehung) → new /modul/3/
# Old /modul/3/ (Erschöpfung) → new /modul/4/
# Old /modul/4/ (Loyalität) → new /modul/5/
# Old /modul/5/ (Handeln) → new /modul/6/
# Old /modul/6/ (Resilienz) → new /modul/7/
# Old /modul/7/ (Ressourcen) → new /modul/8/
# Server-side redirects for old URLs 2-7 are NOT possible because
# the new module numbers 2-7 now serve different content at those paths.
# Visitors with old bookmarks to /modul/2/ will land on the new Modul 2 (Belastung),
# which is closely related to the old Modul 1 content they may have bookmarked.

